in 2019 the @nationalportraitgallery acquired six of my photographs including this one of @skepta #greatness

and after a three year refurbishment, this photograph of @stormzy and his mum is hanging on their walls. Thanks to @nicholascullinan for understanding the power of photography which makes a significant impact in the new exhibitions. This is pretty landmark stuff for me. 🖼️ @nationalportraitgallery

it’s great to see the new curation of the space getting its flowers! But also, there’s more work to do in representation. It’s not just the sitters who should (and have) been diversified, it’s the artists too. So I raise my glass to a future that is full of acquisitions of the work of black artists!

Portrait of @julieadenuga @nationalportraitgallery

amazing @joy_bc my friend my hero my artist nerd off companion, has created another absolute masterpiece… Colonna 2023 (so joy it hurts)
using pigment and the artists hands, we have created these incredible images of her amazing work. Precious Tears… a favourite. Head over to @joy_bc to grasp the true meaning of these pieces
@joy_bc is having her first solo show in NYC during New York Jewelry week at @lesenluminures where you can see this incredible piece on display

like all good relationships… it started with a piss. or more specifically, on a particularly hard location shoot in Hackney Wick where I looked more than a little bit homeless, being told by the host @cornerstonehackney that I couldn’t come in to the establishment to do a wee…

but like all good artist muse stories, somehow @cheftombrown convinced me that I was welcome, even inviting me to piss in a pan or in fact just drop my pants and piss on the floor. that’s the kind of attitude i respect. so when I heard about the launch of the @pearlyqueenshoreditch I quickly decided I would exact my revenge by making him dress in a hugely over the top suit, designed by me and painstakingly embellished by the true east-ender that is my mum @morrisonstylist #pearlyking for the #pearlyqueen

and tonight, on the night of the @pearlyqueenshoreditch launch itself, I am pleased to say that @cheftombrown and i are still bonding over what can happen when you throw genitalia into the mix. in this case, vulvas made from oyster shells, much like the tattoo he has on the back of his head, which looks very much like what Tom would refer to as a “minge”. So after a few months of hard work and a blossoming friendship, I’m pleased to say I’ve finished sanding my clits and polishing my labia and we are ready to show off our bespoke sculptures to the world… images coming soon… go buy our vaginas, they’re all for sale 🦪

I know everyone has been gagging to see my oyster shell vulvas for @pearlyqueenshoreditch 

Let’s start with “Goldie”
A comment on golden showers? Perhaps. She’s seasoned with 24ct burnished gold leaf and has a precious citrine “drip” - all sculptures framed in delicious oak box frames on a bed of oyster silk, POA from @pearlyqueenshoreditch with thanks to @joy_bc for skill sharing and @cheftombrown for going with my madness

then there was “Anjuli”
the vulva with class, she has a pink tourmaline clitoris, surrounded by 24ct gold, her glazed shell holds a dried and glazed orchid. POA at @pearlyqueenshoreditch where they hang in delicious hand stained oak box frames, mounted on oyster silk by @theframingroom (with thanks to @joy_bc)

and here we have “Yuki”
a cheeky little pierced vulva, with seven gold plated titanium rings and bars, lovingly secured by @fleshformers_london around her glazed shell. POA from @pearlyqueenshoreditch - she comes In a hand stained oak box frame, mounted on oyster silk, by @theframingroom

and then there was “Stevie”
With her extended clitoris topped with 24ct gold ring and pink freshwater pearl, glazed oyster shell and repositioned barnacle mons. POA from @pearlyqueenshoreditch and framed in hand stained oak box frame by @theframingroom with thanks to @joy_bc for affixing her pearl

this is “Olivia”
not a vulva shell, but can be a bit of a pussy when she’s not being a bad bitch (you know you’ve missed an on feed selfie)

and last but not least our “Tracy”
a glazed shell with strings of tiny freshwater pearls, that also drip from her glazed and dried orchid petals. POA from @pearlyqueenshoreditch she is framed in an oak box frame and mounted on oyster silk by @theframingroom
